        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 8:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 827 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Colstrip, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip and Hathaway.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
